x4freetext: Scattering of 14.1 MeV neutrons by B-10
Physique Nucleaire de l`Universite de Lausanne.
.Two different scatterers, each measuring 7.2 cm high,
1.8 cm wide and 5 cm thick, were used alternately, the
center of the scatterer being placed along the neutron
beam axis, 18 cm from the source.
Spectra by means of fast spectrometer employing
the associated alpha particles from the H-3(d,n)He-4
.The fast-slow coincidence circuitry as well as the
time-to-pulse-height converter used are described by
Angular resolution +- 4.5 deg. Time resolution for
direct flight 1.9 ns (FWHM), flight path, depending
on the mean scattering angle, 4 to 5 m.
